            "difficulty": "easy",

            "descriptive_text": "An online shop sells products to registered customers. Each customer can place multiple orders but an order always belongs to exactly one customer. Each order consists of one or more order lines. Each order line refers to exactly one product and stores the ordered quantity. A product can appear in many order lines across different orders. After an order is completed the shop generates exactly one invoice for that order. Each invoice belongs to exactly one order. Each invoice contains one or more invoice lines and every invoice line corresponds to exactly one order line. Products are grouped into categories and each product belongs to exactly one category while a category can contain many products.",

